  "wikitext": "{{Navbutton/Separation}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|canBeBurned=1\n|foodType = [[Food Type#Meat|Meat]] {{Pic|32px|Meats|Food Type#Meat}}\n|foodRecipe = {{Pic|32px|Meats}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Filler}}x3\n|image = Meatballs Dropped.png\n|icon = <gallery>\nMeatballs.png|Normal\nMeatballs (Pig Fiesta).png|Pig Fiesta\n</gallery>\n|hpRestored     = 3\n|hungerRestored = 62.5\n|sanityRestored = 5\n|cooktime       = 15 sec\n|priority       = -1\n|spoil          = 10 Days\n|stack          = 40\n|soldBy         ={{Ham}}: {{Pic|32|The Sterling Trough Deli}} ({{Pic|24|Oinc}} &times;10)\n|spawnCode      = \"meatballs\"\n}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = I cooked it myself!\n|willow = Meat made into spheres and improved with fire.\n|wolfgang = Ball of meats make me strong!\n|wendy = Balled meat. How exciting.\n|wx78 = MEAT PACKED INTO THE MOST NUTRITIOUS SHAPE: SPHERES\n|wickerbottom = A pile of processed meat. Who knows what went into this.\n|woodie = All the meats!\n|maxwell = My compliments to the chef!\n|wagstaff = These round spheres of meat should be digestible.\n|wigfrid = Tiny feast balls.\n|webber = I used to make these with grandpa!\n|walani = Saucy.\n|warly = I'm having a ball!\n|woodlegs = Me lunch!\n|wilba = 'TIS BALLS O' MEAT!\n|wormwood = Balls of belly stuff\n|wheeler = Perfectly rounded edible projectiles.\n|winona = Don't mind if I do.\n|wortox = Physical food is so hilarious.\n|wurt = Glurgh... hunks of yuck.\n|walter = They're the best part of spaghetti anyway.\n|wanda = Meat in a ball, quick and to the point.\n|choose = wolfgang\n}}\n\n'''Meatballs''' is a [[Meats|Meat]] [[Food]] [[item]] cooked in the [[Crock Pot]] by combining any Meats and fillers excluding [[Inedibles]]. However, adding 3.0 units of Meats will result in [[Meaty Stew]] instead. It takes 15 seconds to cook.\n\nAdding 2 or more [[Monster Food]]s will result in [[Monster Lasagna]], unless [[Twigs]] are also added, which will then result in [[Wet Goop]]. Adding [[Honey]] will result in [[Honey Nuggets]] or [[Honey Ham]]. Adding a [[Mandrake]] will result in [[Mandrake Soup]]. Adding [[Eggplant]] and another [[Vegetables|Vegetable]] will result in [[Stuffed Eggplant]]. Using less than 1.0 units of Meats ''and'' using at least two [[Ice]] as fillers will result in [[Bunny Stew]].\n\nMeatballs are a decent starter recipe for [[Hunger]], especially when only working with [[Monster Meat|monster meat.]] There are better alternatives, such as [[Meaty Stew]], [[Honey Ham]], [[Bacon and Eggs]], that provide more [[Health]] and [[Hunger]] gain, or longer spoilage time. Attention should be paid to the ingredients used as depending on the recipe, meatballs may provide little to no hunger over their components (e.g. 1 Meat and 3 Carrots will provide no additional hunger).\n\n== Prerequisites ==\n* Requires: [[File:Meats Crock Pot.png|link=Meats]]\n* Excludes: [[File:Twigs.png|link=Twigs]]\n* Excludes: [[File:Weevole Carapace.png|frameless|60x60px|link=Weevole_Carapace]]\n\n== {{pic|32|Cookbook}} Recipe ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Meats\n|item2 = Filler\n|count2 = 3\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Meatballs\n}}\n\n== Example ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Monster Meats\n|item2 = Red Cap\n|count2 = 3\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Meatballs\n|note={{Pic24|Prototype}} A recipe for Meatballs that extracts a lot of useful hunger value out of harmful ingredients}}{{Recipe\n|item1 = Morsels\n|item2 = Berry\n|count2 = 3\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Meatballs\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Morsels\n|item2 = Morsels\n|item3 = Morsels\n|item4 = Morsels\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Meatballs\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Raw Fishes\n|item2 = Roasted Seaweed\n|item3 = Seaweed\n|item4 = Halved Coconut\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Meatballs\n|dlc = Shipwrecked\n|note = Using exactly two raw [[Seaweed]] will produce [[California Roll]] instead.\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Meats\n|item2 = Kelp Fronds\n|count2 = 3\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Meatballs\n|dlc = DST\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Leafy Meats\n|item2 = Berry\n|item3 = Carrots\n|item4 = Ice\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Meatballs\n|dlc = Don't Starve Together\n}}\n{{Recipe|\nitem1 = Meats\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Ice\n|item4 = Ice\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Meatballs\n|note=Creates [[Bunny Stew]] if Meats value is less than 1.0\n|dlc = Don't Starve Together\n}}\n\n\n== {{Pic32|Placeholder}} Trivia ==\n* During the [[Pig Fiesta]] event in the ''[[Don't Starve: Hamlet|Hamlet]]'' DLC, Meatballs take on a more festive appearance.\n\n== {{pic32|Blueprint}} Gallery ==\n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" hideaddbutton=\"true\">\nValentines 2018 2.png|Meatballs as seen on the 2018 Valentine Cards.\nCD meatballs.png|Original HD icon from Bonus Materials from [[CD Don't Starve]].\nMeatballs 128x128.png|Icon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord\nMeatballs (Pig Fiesta).png|Meatballs in Pig Fiesta\n</gallery>\n\n{{Crock Pot Food}}\n__NOTOC__\n[[fr:Boulettes de viande]]\n[[vi:Thịt Viên]]\n[[pt:Almôndegas (Meatballs)]]\n[[Category:Crock Pot Recipes]]\n[[Category:Food]]\n[[Category:Flammable Objects]]\n[[Category:Healing]]\n[[Category:Meats]]\n[[Category:Perishables]]\n[[Category:Sanity Boost]]"
